💻 Mini Project – Network Report

Create network-report.sh

#!/bin/bash

REPORT="network-report.txt"

echo "===== Network Report =====" > $REPORT
echo "Generated: $(date)" >> $REPORT
echo "" >> $REPORT

echo "Hostname:" >> $REPORT
hostname >> $REPORT

echo "" >> $REPORT

echo "IP Address:" >> $REPORT
hostname -I >> $REPORT

echo "" >> $REPORT

echo "Routes:" >> $REPORT
ip route >> $REPORT

echo "" >> $REPORT

echo "DNS:" >> $REPORT
cat /etc/resolv.conf >> $REPORT

echo "" >> $REPORT

echo "Listening Ports:" >> $REPORT
ss -tuln >> $REPORT

echo "Report saved to $REPORT"
📖 notes.md
# Linux Networking Notes

IP Address → Device identifier on a network.

Gateway → Router used to reach other networks.

DNS → Resolves domain names into IP addresses.

TCP → Reliable communication.

UDP → Faster, connectionless communication.

Port → Logical endpoint for communication.

CIDR → Network address notation.
